@Section
    @Title { Qt Assistant in More Detail }
    @Tag { qt.assistant.in.more.detail }
@Begin
@BeginSubSections
@SubSection
    @Title { The Sidebar }
    @Tag { the.sidebar }
@Begin
@LP
The sidebar provides three ways of navigating documentation:

@BulletList
@LI{
The @Option{Contents} tab presents a tree view of the documentation
sets that are available. If you click an item, its documentation
will appear in the documentation window. If you double click
an item or click a '+' sign to the left of an item, the item's
sub-items will appear. Click a sub-item to make its page appear
in the documentation window. Click a '-' sign to the left of
an item to hide its sub-items.
}
@LI{
The @Option{Index} tab is used to look up key words or phrases. See
@TitlePageRef{the.minute.guide.to.using.qt.assistant} for how to use this
tab.
}
@LI{
The @Option{Bookmarks} tab lists any bookmarks you've made. Double
click a bookmark to make its page appear in the documentation
window. The @Option{Bookmarks} tab has a @Option{New Bookmark} button and
a @Option{Delete Bookmark} button at the bottom. Click @Option{New Bookmark}
to bookmark the page that is showing in the documentation window.
Click a bookmark in the list, then click @Option{Delete Bookmark}
to delete the highlighted bookmark.
}
@LI{
The @Option{Search} tab provides full text search of @I{all} the documents.
For further information see @TitlePageRef{full.text.searching}.
}
@EndList

If you want the documentation window to use as much space as possible,
you can easily hide or show the Sidebar. If the Sidebar is showing,
press @Option{Ctrl+T}, @Option{Ctrl+I}, @Option{Ctrl+B} or
@Option{Ctrl+S} to hide it. If the Sidebar is hidden, press
@Option{Ctrl+T} to show it on the Contents tab, or press
@Option{Ctrl+I} to show it on the Index tab (with the focus in the
'Look For' line edit box), or press @Option{Ctrl+B} to show it on the
Bookmarks tab, or press @Option{Ctrl+S} to show it on the (full text)
Search tab.

@PP
The Sidebar is a dock window, so you can drag it to the top,
left, right or bottom of @QAT's window, or you can
drag it outside @QAT to float it.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { The Toolbar }
    @Tag { the.toolbar }
@Begin
@LP
The toolbar provides fast access to the most common actions.

@TaggedList labelwidth { 5f }
@TagItem{
@Option{Previous}}{ Takes you to the previous page. The menu option
is @Option{Go"|"Previous} and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Alt+Left Arrow}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Next}}{ Takes you to the next page. The menu option is @Option{Go"|"Next}
and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Alt+Right Arrow}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Home}}{ Takes you to the home page (normally the home page of
the Qt Reference Documentation). The menu option is @Option{Go"|"Home}
and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl+Home}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Copy}}{ Copies any selected text to the clipboard. The menu
option is @Option{Edit"|"Copy} and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl+C}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Find in Text}}{ Invokes the @Win{Find Text} dialog. The menu option
is @Option{Edit"|"Find in Text} and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl+F}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Print}}{ Invokes the @Win{Print} dialog. The menu option is @Option{File"|"Print}
and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl+P}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Zoom in}}{ Increases the font size. The menu option is @Option{View"|"Zoom in} and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl++}.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Zoom out}}{ Decreases the font size. The menu option is @Option{View"|"Zoom out} and the keyboard shortcut is @Option{Ctrl+-}.
}
@EndList

The remaining toolbar buttons are bookmarks and will vary depending
on your configuration.

@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { The Menus }
    @Tag { the.menus }
@Begin
@BeginSubSubSections
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The File Menu }
    @Tag {the.file.menu}
@Begin
@TaggedList labelwidth { 9f }
@TagItem{
@Option{File"|"Print}}{ Invokes the @Win{Print} dialog.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{File"|"Exit}}{ Terminates @QAT.
}
@EndList
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Edit Menu }
    @Tag{the.edit.menu}
@Begin
@TaggedList labelwidth { 9f }
@TagItem{
@Option{Edit"|"Copy}}{ Copies any selected text to the clipboard.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Edit"|"Find in Text}}{ Invokes the @Win{Find Text} dialog.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Edit"|"Settings}}{ Invokes the @Win{Settings} dialog.
}
@EndList
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The View Menu }
    @Tag{the.view.menu}
@Begin
@TaggedList labelwidth { 9f }
@TagItem{
@Option{View"|"Zoom in}}{ Increases the font size.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{View"|"Zoom out}}{ Decreases the font size.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{View"|"Views"|"Sidebar}}{ Toggles the display of the Sidebar.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{View"|"Views"|"Toolbar}}{ Toggles the display of the Toolbar.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{View"|"Views"|"Line up}}{ Lines up the toolbar buttons in the
Toolbar.
}
@EndList
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Go Menu }
    @Tag{the.go.menu}
@Begin
@TaggedList labelwidth { 9f }
@TagItem{
@Option{Go"|"Previous}}{ Display the previous page.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Go"|"Next}}{ Display the next page.
}
@TagItem{
@Option{Go"|"home}}{ Go to the home page.
}
@EndList

This menu also has additional items; these are pre-defined bookmarks
that vary depending on your configuration.
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Bookmarks Menu }
    @Tag{the.bookmarks.menu}
@Begin
@TaggedList labelwidth { 9f }
@TagItem{
@Option{Bookmarks"|"Add}}{ Add the current page to the list of bookmarks.
}
@EndList

This menu may have additional items, i.e. any bookmarks that
you have already made. If you want to delete a bookmark go to
the Bookmarks tab on the Sidebar.
@End @SubSubSection
@EndSubSubSections
@End @SubSection
@SubSection
    @Title { The Dialogs }
    @Tag { the.dialogs }
@Begin
@BeginSubSubSections
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Print Dialog }
    @Tag{the.print.dialog}
@Begin
@LP
This dialog is platform-specific. It gives access to various
printer options and can be used to print the current page.
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Find Text Dialog }
    @Tag{the.find.text.dialog}
@Begin
@LP
This dialog is used to find text in the current page. Enter the
text you want to find in the Find line edit. If you check the
'Whole words only' checkbox, the search will only consider whole
words, i.e. if you search for 'spin' with this checkbox checked
it will not match 'spinbox', but will match 'spin'. If you check
the 'Case sensitive' check box then, for example, 'spin' will
match 'spin' but not 'Spin'. You can search Forward or Backward
from your current position in the page by clicking one of the
Direction radio buttons. Click the @Option{Find} button to search
(or search again), and click the @Close button to finish.
@End @SubSubSection
@SubSubSection
    @Title { The Settings Dialog }
    @Tag{the.settings.dialog}
@Begin
@LP
This dialog is used to set your preferences for @QAT.
In order to confirm your changes click @OK; or click @Cancel
to keep the previous settings. @QAT will remember
your settings between sessions, including window sizes and positions,
and which pages you have open. The Settings dialog contains the
following tabs:

@BulletList
@LI{ @I{General Settings} --- To change the base font used throughout
@QAT, select a font type from the Font combobox. To choose a new
fixed-width font, to show code snippets for example, choose a font
type from the 'Fixed font' combobox. To change the color of hypertext
links, click the 'Link color' color button. Uncheck the 'Underline
links' checkbox if you don't want underlined links.
}
@LI{ @I{Web Settings} --- Some pages contain links to external web
pages. In order to display these links, you must specify a web
browser. Click @Option{Browse} to invoke the @I{Assistant} dialog and
navigate until you find the web browser you wish to use. Click
@OK to accept the selection. Alternatively, type in the name
of your browser's executable in the line edit.
}
@LI{ @I{Documentation} --- To add your own documentation to @QAT, click
@Option{Add} to invoke the @Win{Assistant} dialog. Navigate through
the files until you find the documentation you want to add and then
click @OK. Click @Option{Delete} to remove obsolete
documentation from the Documentation list box. Read more about adding
your own documentation in
@TitlePageRef{adding.documentation.to.qt.assistant}.
}
@LI{ @I{Categories} --- All documentation is categorized, for example,
development, office, multimedia, etc. To create a new category, type
its name in the Category Name line edit and click @Option{Add}. The
new category appears in the Categories list box with a checkbox to its
left. Leave the box checked to display all of the category's available
documentation. To remove a category, select it from the list box and
click @Option{Delete}. For further information about categories read
@TitlePageRef{adding.documentation.to.qt.assistant}.}
@EndList
@End @SubSubSection
@EndSubSubSections
@End @SubSection
@EndSubSections
@End @Section
